Messaging for In-App and Web

A Messaging for In-App or Web session ends when the agent selects End Chat. If a customer continues to send messages, a new session is created. The conversation continues seamlessly from the customer’s perspective, but the agent loses access to the original pre-chat data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience.
This article applies to: Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels

To set up Omni-Channel Flow and Messaging:
Customize Application
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets

Before you begin, you must have an Omni-Channel flow that already handles pre-chat data. To store this data, update your Omni-Channel flow to access it from subsequent sessions using the ConversationId field of the Messaging Session record.

IMPORTANT This scenario is more likely to occur in Messaging for In-App where a customer can continue a conversation long after the agent has ended the chat.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Flows, and then select Flows.
Find and select your previous flow from the list.
Add a check to determine if we have a pre-existing session from the same conversation. If so, use that information to repopulate the input variables.
Use a Get Records element to get the current messaging session using the recordId input.
Use a Decision Tree element and check if the previous result is null.
If this session is the first messaging session, no action is necessary.
If this session isn’t the first messaging session, extract the pre-chat information from wherever you previously stored it and put it in the correct input variables.

The following screenshot illustrates what your new flow could look like. The new logic is highlighted.
Click Done.
Save this flow as a new version, and verify that it’s activated in your org.
title: Preserving Pre-Chat Data in Service Cloud
